.\" ftr.1.in — man page placeholder for ftr(1).
.\"
.\" Phase 6 fills this in once real subcommand bodies land. For now
.\" it documents the surface so packagers building from this skeleton
.\" don't get confused.
.\"
.TH FTR 1 "@DATE@" "feather @VERSION@" "Peacock OS Manual"
.SH NAME
ftr \- Peacock OS package manager (feather)
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B ftr
.RI < command >
.RI [ options ]
.br
.B ftr
.RB { \-\-help | \-\-version }
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B feather
(invoked as
.BR ftr )
manages the Peacock OS platform layer, user apps, and runtime compat
shims that sit on top of the base distro (Arch, Debian, Alpine, ...).
The base distro's package manager continues to own
.IR /usr ,
.IR /etc ,
.IR /var ,
and
.IR /home ;
feather writes only within
.IR /peacock ,
.IR /apps ,
.IR /compat ,
.IR /data ,
plus
.I /etc/feather/
and
.IR /var/lib/feather/ .
.SH COMMANDS
.TP
.B install
Install one or more packages.
.TP
.B remove
Remove an installed package.
.TP
.B sync
Refresh repository metadata.
.TP
.B upgrade
Upgrade installed packages.
.TP
.B search
Search repositories for a package.
.TP
.B info
Show package metadata.
.TP
.B list
List installed packages.
.TP
.B files
List files owned by an installed package.
.TP
.B flavor
Report the active Peacock base flavor.
.SH FILES
.TP
.I /etc/feather/feather.conf
Main configuration file.
.TP
.I /var/lib/feather/local/
Local install database.
.TP
.I /var/lib/feather/sync/
Cached remote repository metadata.
.TP
.I /var/lib/feather/gpg/
Trusted repository signing keys.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR pacman (8),
.BR apt (8),
.BR apk (8)
.SH BUGS
This is the phase 2 skeleton. Every subcommand currently prints
\(lqnot implemented yet\(rq and exits 0.
